-- Riyad Bank Third-Quarter Profit Falls 24% as Commission Income Declines
-- B y   I n a l   E r s a n
-- 2010-10-13T12:47:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-13/riyad-bank-third-quarter-profit-falls-24-as-commission-income-declines.html
Riyad Bank posted a decline in
third-quarter profit to 611 million riyals from 759 million
riyals in the year-ago period on lower income from commissions
and due to the conservative policy of the lender.  The Saudi bank announced its quarterly results through the
Saudi bourse today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
